  "prompt": "How do you find out the status of an SFSU application?",
  "response": "To check the status of an SFSU (San Francisco State University) application, you can:\n\n1. Log in to the CSU Mentor website (www.csumentor.edu) where you initially submitted your application.\n\n2. Visit the SFSU Admissions website and look for the application status check portal.\n\n3. Contact the SFSU Admissions Office directly:\n- Phone: (415) 338-1111\n- Email: admissions@sfsu.edu\n\n4. Check your email associated with the application for any updates or communications from the university.\n\n5. If you created an online account during the application process, use those login credentials to check your application status.\n\nHave your application number or student ID ready when checking your status. The specific steps may vary slightly depending on when you applied and the current application cycle.",
